definition.value: An agent that reduces or interferes with the mutagenic actions or effects of a substance.
An agonist that binds to and activates abscisic acid receptors.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of protoporphyrinogen oxidase, EC 1.3.3.4.
Any compound that inhibits one or more steps in the pathway leading to the synthesis of gibberellins.
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of the enzyme methionine gamma-lyase (EC 4.4.1.11).
Any acid anhydride hydrolase inhibitor that inhibits the action of H(+)-transporting two-sector ATPase inhibitor, EC 3.6.3.14.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of any hydrolase that acts on an acid anhydride (EC 3.6.*.*).
An inhibitor of NF-kappaB (nuclear factor kappa-light-chain-enhancer of activated B cells), a protein complex involved in the transcription of DNA.
A cyclooxygenase inhibitor with specificity for cyclooxygenase 3.
Any compound that inhibits oxidative phosphorylation.
An inhibitor that interferes with the action of sodium-glucose transport protein subtype 2.
A hormone antagonist that inhibits the action of the peptide hormone cholecystokinin.
An agonist at the A2A receptor.
An agonist at any adenosine receptor.
An agonist at the adenosine A3 receptor.
An acaricide that kills mites of the genus Sarcoptes.
A hormone agonist that binds to and activates a thyroid hormone receptor.
A photochemical role realized in the absorption of ultraviolet light, for example to protect skin cells from damage.
A drug used in treating and healing of wounds.
Any agent used to determine the amino-acid sequence in a polypeptide.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of creatine kinase, EC 2.7.3.2.
Any enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of methionyl aminopeptidase (EC 3.4.11.18).
Any methionyl aminopeptidase inhibitor that inhibits the action of methionyl aminopeptidase 2.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates cannabinoid receptors.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates type 1 cannabinoid receptors.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates type 2 cannabinoid receptors.
A reagent used in the determination by spectrophotometry of the concentration of a chemical element or chemical compound in solution.
A substance that invokes a specific immune non-responsiveness due to its molecular form. If its molecular form is changed, a tolerogen can become an immunogen.
A reagent used to couple amino acids during artificial peptide synthesis.
A PPAR modulator which activates the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-beta/delta.
Any compound that inhibits the growth of bacteria of the genus Vibrio.
An antimetabolite that impairs the action of folic acids
An effector that binds to and activates the enzyme nitric oxide synthase (EC 1.14.13.39)
Any substance that stimulates the corneal nerves in the eves to cause tears.
Substance used to set dyes on fabrics or tissue sections by forming a coordination complex with the dye which then attaches to the fabric or tissue.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of ribonucleoside-diphosphate reductase (EC 1.17.4.1).
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the activity of sepiapterin reductase (EC 1.1.1.153), which plays an important part in the biosynthesis of tetrahydrobiopterin.
Any compound used as a monomer for a polymerisation process. The term is generally used in relation to industrial polymerisation processes.
An compound that inhibits quinol oxidation sites.
An antagonist at the epidermal growth factor receptor.
Any substance which is used to reduce or control weight.
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of NADP(+)-dependent decarboxylating phosphogluconate dehydrogenase (EC 1.1.1.44).
A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralize the deleterious effects of paracetamol (acetaminophen).
A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralize the deleterious effects of curare.
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of gamma-glutamyltransferase (EC 2.3.2.2).
A compound that causes the contraction of body tissues, typically used to reduce bleeding from minor abrasions.
A compound used as a probe during microarray analysis of oligosaccharide-protein interactions.
A reagent used in the immobilization of compounds prior to their use in microarray analysis.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the activity of gamma-secretase.
An enzyme inhibitor that interfers with the action of ribonuclease T1 (EC 3.1.27.3)
